  <p><strong>Cannabis club membership in Madrid costs €20–€50 one-time, while product contributions range from €6–€15 per gram for flower.</strong> This makes legal club access roughly comparable to street prices, but with verified quality, no legal risk, and a safe environment.</p>

  <h2 id="membership-fees">Membership Fees</h2>

  <p>Based on our visits to cannabis clubs across Madrid, membership fees are the clearest, most transparent cost. These are legitimate association memberships—you're joining a registered collective, not paying an entry fee.</p>

  <p><strong>Most clubs charge €20–€50 for one-time membership.</strong> A handful of premium clubs in Malasaña or Chamberí might charge €60–€100, typically positioning themselves as members-only lounges with imported strains and social spaces. Budget-friendly clubs in less touristy neighborhoods (Vallecas, Villaverde) sometimes charge as little as €15–€20.</p>

  <p>What you get varies by club type:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Budget clubs (€15–€25):</strong> Smaller space, basic selection, functional atmosphere. Zero frills. Good for getting product quickly.</li>
    <li><strong>Mid-range clubs (€30–€50):</strong> Better locations, larger inventory, more comfortable seating. Some have small lounges or games.</li>
    <li><strong>Premium clubs (€60–€100):</strong> Designer interiors, private lounging areas, curated strain selection, sometimes food/drinks available.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>A few clubs don't charge membership at all—they recoup costs through slightly higher product pricing. Always ask upfront rather than assuming.</p>

  <p>Importantly, membership is <strong>one-time</strong> at most legitimate clubs. If a club asks you to "renew" annually, that's a red flag. You pay once, then your membership is valid indefinitely unless you stop visiting for years and they clear inactive members.</p>

